      • invoke

        public static void invoke(AbstractPrototype owner,
          int index,
          ArgumentStack stack)
                   throws java.lang.Throwable
        This method simplifies the invocation of a method in a prototype object.

        Precondition of stack (from top to bottom):

        • argument[n]
        • argument[.]
        • argument[2]
        • argument[1]
        • argument[0]
        • owner

        Postcondition of stack (from top to bottom), if the method returns a non-void type:

        • result

        If the return-type of the method is the void-type, then the postcondition of the stack is empty.

        Parameters:
        owner - is the prototype that contains the method to invoke.
        index - is the index of the method in the prototype's list of members.
        stack - contains the arguments to pass to the method, including the owner object. The stack will also be used to pass the return-value back, if any.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable - in order to propagate exceptions thrown by the method.
